{
    "name": "Burglar",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Burglar",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 210",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 210",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 210
                }
            ],
            "html": "Burglars specialize in breaking and entering to rob homes and businesses. These criminals focus on gaining access to secure buildings and bypassing traps and other security measures while remaining undetected all the while.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 19"
        },
        {
            "name": "Criminals",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Criminal Scams",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Common scams criminals run include sending fake collectors for nonexistent charities to seek donations for the diseased and downtrodden; rigged games of chance at local fairs offering worthless prizes, and flashy sideshows concealing the work of pickpockets in the audience; and plants who offer to help travelers find accommodations but lead them to inns with exorbitant prices."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Fantasy Crimes",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "While many crimes in <i>Pathfinder</i> are similar to crimes in the real world, certain crimes are possible only in a world of magic. These include using magic to win a wager, malicious uses of <a aonid=\"38\" game-obj=\"Traits\">curses</a>, violating autonomy with <a aonid=\"61\" game-obj=\"Traits\">enchantment</a> magic, falsifying <a aonid=\"47\" game-obj=\"Traits\">divinations</a>, violating privacy with divinations, or trespassing via <a aonid=\"156\" game-obj=\"Traits\">teleportation</a>."
                },
                {
                    "name": "More Scams",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "<ul><li>Fraudsters sell fake alchemical items, medicines, charms, talismans, or other minor magics.</li><li>Unscrupulous moneylenders take advantage of lax business regulations to employ predatory repayment terms.</li><li>Phony fortune-tellers and mediums use cold-reading techniques to lull gullible marks.</li></ul>"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Protection Money",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 208
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Criminal organizations often find it easier to demand protection money from locals than go to the trouble of stealing it. \u201cProtection\u201d includes an implicit assumption that those who pay up are safe from those criminals, and some also promise retribution against other criminals."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 208",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 208
                }
            ],
            "html": "Some criminals are the desperate who have no option but to break the law to survive, while others choose a life of crime for thrills, forming gangs or underworld guilds that specialize in certain illegal ventures."
        }
    ],
